							<div class="pdb-story">
								<!--Thumbnail-->
																<div class="image">
									<img src="https://assets.ozy.com/ozy-prod/2019/07/shutterstock_551827573.jpg?width=440&#038;height=440&#038;fit=cover"  width="auto" alt="volkswagen shutterstock 551827573" height="auto" />								</div>
								<!--Headline-->
								<h2>
																			<a href="https://www.ozy.com/presidential-daily-brief/pdb-93856/legal-limit-93847/">
											Ex-Volkswagen CEO Charged With Fraud										</a>
																		</h2>
								<!--Content-->
								<p>German prosecutors have accused Martin Winterkorn of fraud, breach of trust and violation of competition laws over his inaction following revelations in May 2014 that Volkswagen manipulated its <a href="https://www.ozy.com/fast-forward/death-knell-for-diesel-not-so-fast/86369" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">diesel emissions tests</a>. They also claim he failed to alert European and American regulators and customers that VW cars didn’t meet fuel standards. Four others were indicted alongside the disgraced CEO on lesser charges.</p>
<p><strong>What’s in store for Winterkorn? </strong>While he’s unlikely to be extradited to the U.S. to face similar charges, the German fraud indictment alone carries a maximum sentence of 10 years.</p>							</div>
							<div class="pdb-meta">
								<h3 class="short-title">
									Legal Limit								</h3>
								<div class="time-meta">
									<span class="important">Important</span>
																										</div>
																	<div class="read-more">
										<span>Sources:</span>
										<div class="tags">
																							<a href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/greggardner/2019/04/15/ex-volkswagen-ceo-winterkorn-faces-new-criminal-charges-in-germany/#65c52da87d9a" target="_blank">Forbes</a>
																								<a href="https://www.cnn.com/2019/04/15/business/winterkorn-volkswagen-diesel-fraud-charges/index.html" target="_blank">CNN</a>
																						</div>
