																<div class="image">
									<img src="https://assets.ozy.com/ozy-prod/2019/07/shutterstock_1306826389.jpg?width=440&#038;height=440&#038;fit=cover"  width="auto" alt="shutterstock 1306826389" height="auto" />								</div>
								<!--Headline-->
								<h2>
																			<a href="https://www.ozy.com/presidential-daily-brief/pdb-93856/throwback-93866/">
											Lyft Looks to the Past With Airport Taxi Line										</a>
																		</h2>
								<!--Content-->
								<p>With customers and drivers alike flustered by the difficulty of airport ride-sharing, the San Francisco-based company is trying something radical at San Diego International Airport next month: It’s going back to the old-fashioned taxi line, where riders and vehicles physically stand and wait their turn. When a rider hops into a Lyft vehicle, they give the driver a four-digit code to sync their smartphones and provide trip information.</p>
<p><strong>How is Lyft performing on the market?</strong> Not well: The company’s under pressure from a stock slide since going public several weeks ago.</p>
<p><em>Don’t miss <a href="https://www.ozy.com/need-to-know/when-tech-ipos-arent-as-public-as-they-seem/93794" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">OZY’s Special Briefing</a> on this year’s tech IPOs.</em></p>							</div>
